Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Board
    Class that allows creation, modification and access to a board.
    Cell
    Class to store and access values associated with an individual cell, containing information such as a cell's correct value, input value and draft value.
    Position
    Refers to a position on the board by its row and column
    Removalist
    Interface to evaluate whether a point can be removed based on conditions
    UniqueChecker<E>
    This interface is given a game space, and checks if the board has a single unique solution
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CellLocation
    Refers to a position on the board by its row and column
    OptionPanes
    A class to help create various types of option pane pop ups
    SudokuBoard
    Class that allows creation, modification and access to a Sudoku board.
    SudokuBoardCell
    Class to store and access values associated with an individual cell on a board of cells.
    SudokuBoardFiller
    Class that is passed a board of type Board and fills the board with numbers that are appropriate for a sudoku puzzle (see SudokuMain for this description)
    SudokuCellRemover
    This class takes a Board object and removes values from the filled board
    SudokuCellRemoverExhaustive
    This class takes a Board object that has been previously filled and removes values that can be whilst still maintaining a unique solution
    SudokuCellRemoverHard
    This class takes a Board object that has been previously filled and removes values if they cannot be placed anywhere else in the square
    SudokuCellRemoverSimple
    This class takes a Board object that has been previously filled and removes values if all other numbers are somewhere in the same row, column or square
    SudokuFrame
    SudokuGUI creates the GUI for Board (implemented by SudokuBoard)
    SudokuGenerator
    Class that is passed a board of type Board and generates an appropriate sudoku puzzle that is uniquely solveable and has the appropriate number of squares removed
    SudokuMain
    Creates a Sudoku Game Sudoku is a common game played on a 9x9 grid of squares consisting of 9 smaller 3x3 puzzles which the aim is to fill in all blank square in the grid such that there is only one instance of each number from 1 to 9 in each smaller 3x3 square, each row and each column.
    SudokuManager
    Class that manages the construction of both the graphical interface and board generation.
    SudokuSolver
    Class Description
